 <text>
  <front>
   <head>CLOE to LYSANDER.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">OF vagrant loves, and fickle flames</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Lysander's Muse may tell,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And sure such artless freedom claims</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">His Cloe's best farewel.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Whene'er his heart becomes the theme</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">We see his fancy shine;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But let not vain Lysander dream</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">That e'er that heart was mine.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Can he that fondly hopes to move,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">With caution chill his lay?</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Can he who feels the power of love,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Foretel that love's decay?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Why teize believing nymphs in vain?</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Go seek some pathless vale,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And listen to thy vocal strain</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Soft echoing down the dale.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">While artless Cloe hence retir'd,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Shall this sad maxim prove;</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">No bosom, once with love inspir'd,</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Could ever cease to love.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
